      <item>
        <title>Feedback sort: Campus RPG</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[@jasoncordova]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
          <p><a href="https://forums.gauntlet-rpg.com/u/jasoncordova">@jasoncordova</a> wrote:</p>
          <blockquote>
              <p>What an interesting premise for a game! It actually appeals to me in a really personal way. When I was in college, the school I went to had that brutalist architecture—totally oppressive, but also suggestive of something deeper. I always had similar fantasies, as if there was something going on beneath the surface. I think it was significant that my school was largely students of color but that the administration and faculty were predominantly white. That gave the whole thing an even more oppressive vibe.</p>
<p>I’m excited to see where you go with this!</p>
          </blockquote>
          <p><a href="https://forums.gauntlet-rpg.com/t/feedback-sort-campus-rpg/742/17">Read full topic</a></p>
        ]]></description>
